
Lambda Function: A small function that can take any number of arguments, but we don't need
to write a return to give a value.

example
Here lambda function return the sum of two arguments a and b.
x = lambda a,b,c : a + b * c

In this example calling lambda function needs three argument.
x(2,3,6)

If we put only 2 arguments we will get a TypeError:
"TypeError: <lambda>() missing 1 required positional argument: 'c'"

